In this article, you will learn how to set an image, string, or emoji as a list item marker and some tips to better style and organize your list items.
comma separated list


This is the code required to craft a comma separated list.
li:not(:last-child)::after{
      content: ',';
   }


alpha list


You can set list style type to lower-alpha or upper-alpha to keep your list items in an alphabetic order 🇦 🇧 🇨.
li{
  /* list-style-type:upper-alpha; */
     list-style-type:lower-alpha;
}


emoji list


You can set a emoji as a list style type 🌈.

/* <string> value */
list-style-type: '-';

li{
  list-style-type:'🎉';
}


decimal leading zero


Set list style type to decimal leading zero to append leading zero to your ordered list items.
li{
  list-style-type:decimal-leading-zero;
}


marker pseudo element


Marker allows you to style the marker of your list items.
li::marker {
  color: lightgreen;
}


list style image


List style image allows you to specify a image as list item marker box of a list item (bullet, or a number in case of ol)
ul {
  list-style-image: url('linkden.jpg');
}


